fields.title: An Example Post
fields.content: You can add multiple tags by clicking the green plus icon to the right of the tags list. The tag editor opens in a new window.

fields.title: Leo: A Personal Profile
fields.summary: Reload a post detail page in your browser, and provided you have more than one Post object, you should see something like this
fields.content:
The current post that’s being viewed should not be in the list of Recent Posts.
As with a simple tag, we can also pass the context to the inclusion tag function, by adding a context argument and adding takes_context=True to the decorator call.

fields.title: Django vs Python
fields.summary: Next we’ll take a brief look at advanced template tags.
fields.content:
Inclusion tags render faster than regular template tags


You can pass in specific information to the inclusion tag not found in the regular template tag
